    {
      "id": "PopularPost233691",
      "post_content": "This card is not nearly as bad as people are saying. It definitely has its place though not in every deck. I built a red/black sac deck. Unlike most sac decks it's not about repeatedly saccing the same creature (reassembling skeleton) or buffing from saccing (Bloodthrone Vampire), it's about putting creatures on the board that my opponent doesn't want to remove (Goblin Arsonist, Mortis Dogs, Perilous Myr) and using them to chump block my opponent or set up combos with Falkenrath Noble and Rolling Temblor for massive self board wipes. There isn't any room for recession but I wanted to find a way to gain a little extra mileage out of my creatures. This card is that. It lets me turn my creature burn into life gain when I have extra around namely just before I activate a combo or just after. Every time I've gotten it on the field it has changed the game in my favor.  \n  \nThis isn't Mental Misstep or Tragic Slip but it's better than just a 2 star card. ",
      "posted_by": "alphagprime",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost233691\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_post\">This card is not nearly as bad as people are saying. It definitely has its place though not in every deck. I built a red/black sac deck. Unlike most sac decks it's not about repeatedly saccing the same creature (reassembling skeleton) or buffing from saccing (Bloodthrone Vampire), it's about putting creatures on the board that my opponent doesn't want to remove (Goblin Arsonist, Mortis Dogs, Perilous Myr) and using them to chump block my opponent or set up combos with Falkenrath Noble and Rolling Temblor for massive self board wipes. There isn't any room for recession but I wanted to find a way to gain a little extra mileage out of my creatures. This card is that. It lets me turn my creature burn into life gain when I have extra around namely just before I activate a combo or just after. Every time I've gotten it on the field it has changed the game in my favor.<br/><br/>This isn't Mental Misstep or Tragic Slip but it's better than just a 2 star card. </span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '233691'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy78921\">alphagprime</span>\r\n                                (3/18/2012 8:47:37 AM)\r\n  